import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['size'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['size'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['size'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['size'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of size?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['parent'], data['size'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Parent')
    ax.set_ylabel('Size')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between size and parent?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    parent_categories = data.groupby('parent').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    parent_categories = parent_categories.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(parent_categories['parent'], parent_categories['counts'])
    plt.title('What are the most common parent categories?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    names = data['name'].value_counts().to_dict()
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width = 800, height = 800, 
                background_color ='white', 
                min_font_size = 10).generate_from_frequencies(names)
    plt.figure(figsize = (8, 8), facecolor = None) 
    plt.imshow(wordcloud) 
    plt.axis("off") 
    plt.tight_layout(pad = 0) 
    plt.title('What are the most common names in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
